---
import BaseLayout from "@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const updated = "2026-06-19";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Grievance officer"
  description="Mandatory contact under India's IT Rules 2021."
>
  <header class="container mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 pt-12 pb-6 border-b border-neutral-800">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-400 mb-2">
      <a href="/" class="hover:text-neutral-200">Blog</a> /
      <a href="/legal/" class="hover:text-neutral-200">Legal</a> / Grievance officer
    </p>
    <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Grievance officer</h1>
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-500 mt-2">Last updated: {updated}</p>
  </header>

  <article class="container mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 py-10 prose prose-invert">
    <p>
      Per the <strong>Information Technology (Intermediary Guidelines and Digital
      Media Ethics Code) Rules, 2021</strong>, the following contact handles
      complaints related to blog.oriz.in and its sub-sites.
    </p>

    <div class="not-prose my-6 rounded-xl border border-neutral-800 bg-neutral-900/40 p-5">
      <p class="my-1.5"><strong>Name:</strong> Chirag Singhal</p>
      <p class="my-1.5"><strong>Designation:</strong> Grievance Officer</p>
      <p class="my-1.5"><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:whyiswhen@gmail.com" class="text-amber-400 underline">whyiswhen@gmail.com</a></p>
      <p class="my-1.5"><strong>Address:</strong> Bhubaneswar, Odisha, India 751001</p>
      <p class="my-1.5"><strong>Response time:</strong> Acknowledgement within 24 hours; resolution within 15 days.</p>
    </div>

    <h2>What you can report</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Content on blog.oriz.in that infringes your copyright (DMCA / Indian copyright complaints).</li>
      <li>Content that violates the IT Rules (defamation, obscenity, threats, impersonation).</li>
      <li>Privacy concerns under the DPDP Act 2023 — access, correction, deletion of your data.</li>
      <li>Account takeover or security incidents.</li>
    </ul>

    <p>
      Please include: a clear description of the issue, the URL(s) involved,
      proof you are the rights-holder (for copyright), and your contact details.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
